title: For Sale:  BEWARE OF SCAMMERS
postcontent:
Beware of scammers on this site. I have contacted multiple supposed sellers on this site  about AR style firearms they have for sale and all have either been scammers or seem very shady. I have found many posts on ArmsList that have copied pictures from legitimate posts on Gun Broker.

BEWARE IF SELLER WILL NOT RELEASE FIREARM SERIAL NUMBER. NEVER PURCHASE A FIREARM WITHOUT HAVING SERIAL NUMBER IN HAND BEFORE ANY MONEY IS EXCHANGED. SELLER NOT RELEASING SERIAL NUMBER IS AN IMMEDIATE NO-GO.

BEWARE IF SELLER IS NOT WILLING TO GIVE YOU A REAL PHONE NUMBER, ADDRESS, ETC. ASK FOR FULL NAME, ADDRESS, PHONE NUMBER AND GOOGLE CONTACT INFO TO MAKE SURE IT'S CORRECT.

BEWARE IF SELLER WANTS MONEY WIRED. SAFEST WAY TO PAY IS THROUGH AN ESCROW OR BETTER YET, BUY LOCAL AND FACE TO FACE.

BEWARE IF SELLER IS RELUCTANT TO GIVE INFORMATION ABOUT THEM SELF OR THE FIREARM.

BE CAREFUL!

Just to help everybody out.  Check out http://www.gunbot.net/ for ammo. It shows you what a "good deal" is for the current market and you can see what is in stock. This should help you buy ammo without having to pay double what it's worth. 

Also, you can get magpul 30rd AR magazines for $25 in store and like $15-20 if you order them online and can wait 3-4 weeks to get them instead of paying $50-100 bucks a piece. 

Hate to see gun people trying to take advantage of other gun people. Hope this helps out some people.
